15:20.205 --> 15:21.045
Never. No.

15:23.165 --> 15:24.125
It'll make my year.

15:26.645 --> 15:27.925
D'you wanna go have a look?

15:28.365 --> 15:29.445
Yeah. [sighs]

15:30.205 --> 15:31.605
Please bring the new girl.

15:31.685 --> 15:33.765
D'you want to watch us cover this story?

15:34.445 --> 15:35.685
-Yeah. All right.
-[Tony] Yeah?

15:42.965 --> 15:44.205
Here we go.

15:47.765 --> 15:48.605
Here we are.

15:51.565 --> 15:53.485
-[Tony] Fuckin' hell.
-[Brian] Come in.

15:53.885 --> 15:55.445
This is the dining room.

15:57.125 --> 15:58.445
Okay, come through.

16:02.525 --> 16:03.765
[exhales]

16:03.845 --> 16:05.925
This is what I've been talking about.
This is...

16:11.045 --> 16:11.885
Questions?

16:12.525 --> 16:13.685
What's that smell?

16:13.765 --> 16:14.605
Which one?

16:14.685 --> 16:16.525
Like a clawing thing
in the back of the throat.

16:16.605 --> 16:18.125
-Back of the throat. Dead mice.
-Yeah--

16:18.445 --> 16:21.765
Back of the room. Back corner.
Basically, I put some traps there

16:21.845 --> 16:24.325
a couple of years ago,
and I can't get to them, so...

16:25.005 --> 16:26.165
Any other questions?

16:28.165 --> 16:29.605
-What are they?
-Cockroaches.

16:30.445 --> 16:31.325
I collect them.

16:31.405 --> 16:33.525
Basically, these little fellas are, um--

16:33.605 --> 16:34.685
-Don't open it.
-Okay.

16:36.205 --> 16:39.045
My rule is, if you come onto my property,
then I own you.

16:39.485 --> 16:40.325
Okay?

16:41.365 --> 16:42.205
Question three?

16:42.685 --> 16:44.565
-How long have you been doing this?
-Ooh.

16:45.765 --> 16:47.645
When did my wife leave me? [gasps]

16:47.725 --> 16:48.725
Seven years.

16:49.005 --> 16:51.605
Seven years ago. I thought I could
do what I like with the place.

16:52.605 --> 16:53.605
So I just went for it.

16:53.685 --> 16:55.805
Yeah, which brings me to my next question,

16:55.885 --> 16:57.765
-and don't take this the wrong way...
-No.

16:57.845 --> 16:59.565
Why have you never considered suicide?

16:59.645 --> 17:00.485
I have.

17:01.245 --> 17:03.205
And why... didn't you go through with it?

17:03.285 --> 17:05.485
Because I decided it was too good for me.

17:05.765 --> 17:06.605
Wow.

17:07.525 --> 17:09.085
[Brian] That's what you're dealing with.

17:09.645 --> 17:10.925
-Cup of tea?
-Definitely not.

17:11.005 --> 17:11.885
[Brian] Okay.

17:12.685 --> 17:15.765
Brian, this isn't right for a local paper.
How can I do a...

17:16.645 --> 17:18.125
There's no story here, mate.

17:18.205 --> 17:20.165
Can I stay and try and find one?

17:20.885 --> 17:21.965
-[Tony] Really?
-Yeah.

17:22.325 --> 17:23.365
[Tony] Okay.

17:24.325 --> 17:25.285
See you later.

17:26.325 --> 17:27.725
-Cheers, Brian.
-[Len] Yeah.

17:27.805 --> 17:29.205
-[Brian] Thank you.
-Bye.

17:29.285 --> 17:30.125
Where are you going?

17:30.205 --> 17:31.845
-I'm coming with you.
-No, you're not.

17:32.725 --> 17:34.045
[whispering] Don't leave her with him.

17:34.125 --> 17:35.365
-But it stinks.
-Yeah.

17:35.445 --> 17:37.645
[Brian] What d'you wanna know?
Where'd you wanna go?

17:37.725 --> 17:39.485
[Sandy] Just show me
what you've got, really.

17:39.885 --> 17:42.525
[Brian] What I've got? [laughs]
What haven't I got?

17:47.565 --> 17:48.685
Okay, thank you. Yeah.

17:49.325 --> 17:50.645
No, thanks for letting me know.

17:56.925 --> 17:59.925
[silly high voice]
Hello, everybody! Hello!

18:00.005 --> 18:01.925
[silly deep voice]
Hello, everybody! Hello.

18:02.005 --> 18:03.165
Say hello, everybody.

18:03.285 --> 18:04.845
-Hello.
-[silly deep voice] Hello.

18:04.925 --> 18:06.165
[high voice] Hello, Mr. Punch.

18:06.245 --> 18:08.085
[low voice] Hello, Mrs. Punch.
What are you up to?

18:08.165 --> 18:10.365
Oh, nothing much. Nothing much.

18:10.445 --> 18:12.885
Yes, you have.
You've been shagging Mickey the Gypsy.

18:12.965 --> 18:14.085
No, I haven't.

18:14.165 --> 18:15.605
Yes, you have.

18:15.685 --> 18:17.325
Ooh, calm down, Brian.

18:17.405 --> 18:19.565
Calm down?
You're telling me to calm down?

18:19.845 --> 18:21.965
Huh? You've made me a laughing stock
round the village,

18:22.045 --> 18:23.365
and she's telling <i>me</i> to calm down.

18:23.445 --> 18:25.485
She's been shagging anything that moves.

18:25.565 --> 18:28.685
For 18 months, she's shagging
Mickey the Gypsy down Green Lane.

18:29.165 --> 18:31.525
My wife is a slut. There's your headline.

18:31.765 --> 18:32.805
"My Wife's a Slut."

18:33.525 --> 18:35.485
This woman has destroyed me.

18:37.285 --> 18:38.965
Yes, please, take a picture. Thank you.

18:39.365 --> 18:40.205
[camera clicks]

18:49.125 --> 18:50.245
Tony, can I have a word?

18:50.325 --> 18:51.605
-[Tony] Now?
-Yeah, now.

18:55.365 --> 18:56.205
Shut the door.

18:57.405 --> 18:58.365
Sit down.

19:00.725 --> 19:02.325
I just had a phone call from the school.

19:02.565 --> 19:05.085
Not as a story or anything,
but as a parent.

19:05.165 --> 19:07.485
Apparently, a middle-aged man
threatened a ten-year-old child

19:07.565 --> 19:08.445
with a hammer today.

19:10.565 --> 19:12.765
You threatened a child
with a fucking hammer.

19:12.845 --> 19:14.165
Who told you it was me?

19:14.245 --> 19:15.805
Nobody. They don't know it was you.

19:15.885 --> 19:18.085
I know it was you
'cause I've seen the fucking hammer!

19:19.525 --> 19:20.685
He was bullying George.

19:20.765 --> 19:23.245
What the fuck is wrong with you, Tony?
I can't...

19:23.525 --> 19:26.725
I can take all the insults, you know,
the lateness.

19:26.965 --> 19:29.005
Fill your boots with that shit,
but you can't...

19:29.085 --> 19:32.125
If you carry on like this,
people are gonna get hurt, right?

19:32.205 --> 19:33.445
-And it's not gonna be George.
-I know.

19:33.525 --> 19:35.325
I was trying to stop George getting hurt.

19:35.405 --> 19:37.005
I get enough grief from Jill as it is,

19:37.285 --> 19:38.765
letting George see you, but I do it

19:39.085 --> 19:41.245
because I know it makes you happy,

19:41.325 --> 19:44.445
but I can't risk that anymore.
Do you understand?

19:49.605 --> 19:52.125
-I'm fucked up.
-You're not fu... That's not good enough.

19:52.205 --> 19:53.965
That is not good enough, Tony.

19:54.045 --> 19:56.165
That's letting yourself
off the hook again.

19:56.565 --> 19:59.165
People who are fucked up
don't choose to be like that.

19:59.245 --> 20:01.165
You're doing this on purpose.
You know what you're doing.

20:01.245 --> 20:02.725
This is the worst thing you've done.

20:02.805 --> 20:05.285
I don't even know
what you're fighting anymore.

20:05.365 --> 20:08.445
I don't get this, okay?
There is no enemy in this story.

20:08.525 --> 20:10.245
This is... You're doing this to yourself.

20:10.325 --> 20:13.285
I'm in pain, all right?
I'm in fucking pain all the time,

20:13.365 --> 20:14.845
and I do shit like this

20:14.925 --> 20:17.325
[tearfully] 'cause it makes me
feel better for a split second.

20:17.645 --> 20:20.205
Other people are in pain as well.
Other people have shit going on.

20:20.285 --> 20:21.765
Other people have things to deal with.

20:21.845 --> 20:23.685
I just want to be out of pain.

20:23.765 --> 20:26.245
Either live without pain
or die without pain,

20:26.325 --> 20:27.685
whichever one comes first.

20:27.765 --> 20:30.165
-I choose that, all right?
-Okay, listen to me.

20:30.245 --> 20:33.685
If you're saying to me
that you can't be trusted,

20:33.765 --> 20:37.085
that you're not accountable
for your actions, then that's fine,

20:37.165 --> 20:38.525
if that's what you're saying.

20:38.605 --> 20:40.445
But that means
that you don't get to see George.

20:40.925 --> 20:44.725
Because if you're saying I have to choose
between the safety of my son...

20:44.805 --> 20:45.805
and you,

20:45.885 --> 20:49.125
then I choose my son every fucking time.
Do you understand me?

20:49.245 --> 20:50.605
It doesn't even come close.

20:52.165 --> 20:54.845
-I'd never do anything to hurt George.
-Look what you've done already.

20:54.925 --> 20:55.885
I know.

20:56.925 --> 20:58.605
I won't do anything like this again.

20:59.285 --> 21:00.405
Well, let's see, okay?

21:09.245 --> 21:10.965
[Lenny sighs wearily]

21:11.045 --> 21:12.245
What was it like?

21:12.605 --> 21:15.205
-Absolutely mental.
-[Kath] Why?

21:16.165 --> 21:17.365
[Lenny] It's just full of shit.

21:17.445 --> 21:18.525
Just old shit.

21:19.365 --> 21:20.885
He did a puppet show!

21:21.285 --> 21:23.605
-Puppet show?
-Yeah, like an actual puppet show.

21:23.845 --> 21:25.645
How are you even gonna deal
with all of that?

21:25.725 --> 21:26.565
It's quite sad.

21:27.365 --> 21:28.565
Excited to start it.

21:30.245 --> 21:31.445
Why is it empty?

21:32.085 --> 21:33.085
What d'you mean?

21:33.165 --> 21:37.605
Well, usually, there's like a... romantic
scene or a castle or something inside.

21:37.685 --> 21:39.965
[Kath] Yeah. This is one of them
that you're meant to put

21:40.045 --> 21:42.005
a photo of a loved one in, but...

21:42.125 --> 21:43.525
I haven't met anyone, though.

21:44.245 --> 21:45.405
[Tony] Fuck me.

21:46.045 --> 21:47.125
Put something in it.

21:47.925 --> 21:48.965
Picture of your cat,

21:49.685 --> 21:50.685
something you love.

21:51.885 --> 21:52.765
What d'you love?

21:55.245 --> 21:56.125
Loads of stuff.

21:56.405 --> 21:57.245
Go on.

21:58.525 --> 21:59.365
Go on what?

22:01.605 --> 22:03.085
What d'you mean "Go on what"?

22:03.765 --> 22:04.605
What?

22:05.445 --> 22:06.485
I said, "Go on,"

22:08.045 --> 22:09.405
and you said, "Go on what?"

22:10.565 --> 22:12.485
You haven't heard the phrase, "go on,"

22:12.925 --> 22:14.605
as in expound,

22:15.045 --> 22:16.405
give me some examples?

22:17.965 --> 22:19.205
-No.
-No?

22:20.165 --> 22:21.005
Okay.

22:21.565 --> 22:23.685
Give me some examples of things you love.

22:25.285 --> 22:26.205
[Kath exhales]

22:28.485 --> 22:30.405
[sighs] Having a laugh.

22:30.925 --> 22:32.245
-Really?
-[Kath] Yeah!

22:32.805 --> 22:35.045
You've seen the birthday cards
I buy people.

22:35.605 --> 22:37.605
Funny memes I show around on Twitter.

22:39.805 --> 22:40.685
Kevin Hart.

23:02.365 --> 23:04.125
-Fancy seeing you here.
-Oh.

23:05.325 --> 23:06.725
-You all right?
-Yeah.

23:07.445 --> 23:08.285
Good.

23:09.925 --> 23:10.765
Um...

23:11.925 --> 23:12.885
I need some advice.

23:14.085 --> 23:15.285
I wanted to kill myself.

23:16.405 --> 23:18.085
And when I couldn't, or hadn't,

23:19.125 --> 23:20.405
I thought, "Okay.

23:20.725 --> 23:23.765
If I'm gonna do this
carrying on living thing,

23:24.125 --> 23:27.125
it's gonna be on my terms,
I'm gonna do what I want,

23:28.125 --> 23:30.325
and I've always got suicide
to fall back on."

23:31.765 --> 23:33.005
Got to have a backup.

23:33.685 --> 23:34.685
[Tony chuckles]

23:36.005 --> 23:37.165
Exactly.

23:37.645 --> 23:38.925
But it didn't go to plan.

23:39.525 --> 23:40.365
Um...

23:40.885 --> 23:43.285
At first,
I thought it was like a superpower.

23:43.485 --> 23:46.125
I can do <i>anything. </i>Who cares?

23:46.205 --> 23:47.605
What's the worst that can happen?

23:47.685 --> 23:51.205
Nothing can hurt me 'cause I can
always kill myself, you know? And...

23:52.085 --> 23:52.925
But then...

23:53.645 --> 23:54.885
I realized you can't...

23:55.725 --> 23:58.445
You can't not care about things
you actually care about.

23:58.525 --> 24:00.445
You can't fool yourself and...

24:01.325 --> 24:02.445
And, er...

24:02.525 --> 24:06.485
it was something you said,
that it's not all about me,

24:07.645 --> 24:09.085
and even though I'm in pain,

24:10.085 --> 24:10.925
it's worth...

24:12.085 --> 24:14.005
sticking around to maybe...

24:15.125 --> 24:16.005
make my...

24:17.005 --> 24:20.445
little corner of the world
a slightly better place.

24:22.245 --> 24:23.405
That's all there is.

24:26.565 --> 24:28.005
Happiness is amazing.

24:29.405 --> 24:32.165
It's so amazing,
it doesn't matter if it's yours or not.

24:34.245 --> 24:35.565
There's that lovely thing,

24:36.685 --> 24:39.565
"A society grows great
when old men plant trees,

24:39.645 --> 24:42.285
the shade of which they know
they will never sit in."

24:44.245 --> 24:47.285
Good people do things for other people.

24:47.485 --> 24:48.805
That's it. The end.

24:52.405 --> 24:53.605
And you're good, Tony.

24:55.165 --> 24:56.445
You have so much to give.

24:58.645 --> 24:59.605
Smart...

24:59.965 --> 25:00.805
